trans-unit.source: Provides a standard set of media related commands.
trans-unit.target: Fornece um padrão comandos relacionados com o conjunto de suportes de dados.

trans-unit.source: The commands in the MediaCommands class and commands in the other command library classes, such as <xref:System.Windows.Input.ComponentCommands> and <xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands>, are intended to represent a set of common commands that application programmers encounter frequently.
trans-unit.target: Os comandos na classe MediaCommands e comandos no outro comando classes de biblioteca, tais como <xref:System.Windows.Input.ComponentCommands>e <xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands>, destinam-se para representar um conjunto de comandos comuns que os programadores de aplicações ocorrerem com frequência.</xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands> </xref:System.Windows.Input.ComponentCommands>

trans-unit.source: The commands only represent the instance of the <xref:System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand> and not the implementation logic for the command.
trans-unit.target: Os comandos representam apenas a instância do <xref:System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand>e não a lógica de implementação para o comando.</xref:System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand>

trans-unit.source: The implementation logic is bound to the command via a <xref:System.Windows.UIElement.CommandBindings%2A>.
trans-unit.target: A lógica de implementação está vinculada ao comando através de um <xref:System.Windows.UIElement.CommandBindings%2A>.</xref:System.Windows.UIElement.CommandBindings%2A>

trans-unit.source: For example, if the <xref:System.Windows.Input.MediaCommands.Play%2A> command is executed on a control (the command target), the logic which performs the <xref:System.Windows.Input.MediaCommands.Play%2A> command may not be provided by the command target, so the application writer will be responsible for writing the logic that determines how the command target will handle the command.
trans-unit.target: Por exemplo, se o <xref:System.Windows.Input.MediaCommands.Play%2A>comando é executado num controlo (o comando de destino), a lógica que efetua o <xref:System.Windows.Input.MediaCommands.Play%2A>comando não pode ser fornecida de destino de comandos, por isso, o escritor da aplicação será responsável por ao escrever a lógica que determina a forma como o destino de comando irá processar o comando.</xref:System.Windows.Input.MediaCommands.Play%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Input.MediaCommands.Play%2A>

trans-unit.source: Many controls do provide implementation logic for many of the commands in the command library.
trans-unit.target: Controlos muitos fornecer a lógica de implementação para muitos dos comandos na biblioteca de comandos.

trans-unit.source: For example, the <xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBox> class provides logic for the <xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Paste%2A> command, <xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Cut%2A> command, <xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Copy%2A> command, <xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Undo%2A> command, and <xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Redo%2A> command.
trans-unit.target: Por exemplo, o <xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBox>classe fornece lógica para o <xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Paste%2A>comando, <xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Cut%2A>comando, <xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Copy%2A>comando, <xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Undo%2A>comando, e <xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Redo%2A>comando.</xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Redo%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Undo%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Copy%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Cut%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Paste%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBox>

trans-unit.source: For more information on commands and commanding see the [Commanding Overview](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).
trans-unit.target: Para mais informações sobre comandos e consulte commanding o [descrição geral do Commanding](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).
